            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23442",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "test case",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T08:35:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T08:35:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23446",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I tried to work this into a more succinct use case:\n{code}\n<?php\n$translations = array(\n    'foo' => 'Foo Bar!',\n    'boo' => 'Boo Hoo!',\n);\n\n$cacheOptions = array(\n    'frontend' => array(\n        'automatic_serialization' => true,\n        'lifetime' => 3,\n    ),\n    'backend' => array(\n        'cache_db_complete_path' => dirname(__FILE__) . '\/translate.db',\n    ),\n);\n$cache = Zend_Cache::factory('Core', 'Sqlite', $cacheOptions['frontend'], $cacheOptions['backend']);\n\n$local = new Zend_Locale('en_US');\nZend_Translate::setCache($cache);\n$translate = new Zend_Translate('array', $translations, 'en_US');\n\necho $translate->translate('foo');\necho $translate->translate('foo');\nsleep(3);\necho $translate->translate('foo');\nsleep(3);\necho $translate->translate('foo');\n{code}\n\nHowever, this worked fine. It may be an issue with the gettext adapter specifically, and I'll try that next.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:15:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:15:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23447",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The adapter classes themself have no access to the cache.\nThey only read the data and connect them to the abstract class.\n\nThe behaviour of the cache is completly independent of the used adapter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:23:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:23:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23448",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Okay, I tried the following now:\n{code}\n<?php\n$cacheOptions = array(\n    'frontend' => array(\n        'automatic_serialization' => true,\n        'lifetime' => 3,\n    ),\n    'backend' => array(\n        'cache_db_complete_path' => dirname(__FILE__) . '\/translate.db',\n    ),\n);\n$cache = Zend_Cache::factory('Core', 'Sqlite', $cacheOptions['frontend'], $cacheOptions['backend']);\n\n$locale = new Zend_Locale('en');\nZend_Translate::setCache($cache);\n$translate = new Zend_Translate('gettext', dirname(__FILE__) . '\/testcase\/translate\/Application\/Locale\/pl.mo', 'pl');\n\necho $translate->translate('o_object_added');\nsleep(3);\necho $translate->translate('o_object_added');\nsleep(3);\necho $translate->translate('o_object_added');\nsleep(3);\necho $translate->translate('o_object_added');\n{code}\n\nI now get the following exception:\n\n{code}\nPHP Fatal error:  Uncaught exception 'Zend_Translate_Exception' with message 'Error opening translation file '\/home\/matthew\/tmp\/testcase\/translate\/Application\/Locale\/pl.mo'.' in \/home\/matthew\/lib\/framework-full\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Translate\/Adapter\/Gettext.php:88\n{code}\n\nI get this error with or without caching. At this point, I cannot reproduce unless we get a valid translation file to test against.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:24:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:24:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23449",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "default pl  po file",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:31:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:31:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23450",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Question:\n\nAre you changing the locale when using the same cache ?\nBecause actually caching is only done for the complete adapter...\n\nWhen you set the cache and want to load another language afterwards it will not be recognised.\nCaching is only done for the complete adapter at initiation.\n\nYou should add all languages\/files once.\n\n\nThere exists already an issue (ZF-3071) which will add this behaviour (caching on file-basis\/adding translations afterwards to the cache). But it is not implemented for now.\n\n\nThe actual solution is to use a locale-based cache.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:32:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:32:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23451",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "polish mo file",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:34:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:34:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23452",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A po file will not be recognised by Zend_Translate... you should add the related binary gettext file (*.mo)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:35:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:35:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23453",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've run the reproduce case I posted in an earlier comment against the .mo file linked in the issue, and it works both with and without caching.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:38:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:38:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23454",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is the string you wanted to translate available in the mo file ?\nTry to use isTranslated() to verify.\n\nIs the right data loaded ?\nTry to use getList() and getMessages() to verify.\n\nTry the translation itself without application as showed by Matthew to verify if it works or not.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T10:45:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T10:45:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23455",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ergo14",
                        "name": "ergo14",
                        "displayName": "Marcin Lulek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{code}\n<?php\nset_include_path('.' . PATH_SEPARATOR . '.\/Library\/'\n. PATH_SEPARATOR . '.\/Application\/'\n. PATH_SEPARATOR . get_include_path());\nrequire 'Zend\/Registry.php';\nrequire 'Zend\/Cache.php';\n$cache = Zend_Cache::factory('Core', 'File' , array('automatic_serialization' => true, 'lifetime' => 3 ), array('cache_dir' =>'.\/Cache'));\nZend_Registry::set('cache',$cache);\nrequire 'Zend\/Controller\/Front.php';\n$frontController = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Locale.php';\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Translate.php';\n$locale = new Zend_Locale('pl');\nZend_Registry::set('locale', $locale);\nZend_Translate::setCache(Zend_Registry::get('cache'));\nZend_Registry::set('Zend_Translate', new Zend_Translate('gettext', '.\/Application\/Locale\/pl\/default.mo', 'pl'));\necho Zend_Registry::get('Zend_Translate')->translate('mainOptions');\n?>\n{code}\n\nsimplified test case",
